OL,6,FThis rise came despite 3,594 offenders
OL,7,Fbeing deported in Labour's first nine
OL,8,Fmonths in office, a 16% increase on
OL,9,Fthe same period in the previous 12
OL,10,Fmonths.
OL,12,FA combination of early release due to
OL,13,Fprison overcrowding, instability and
OL,14,Fdiplomatic obstruction from some other
OL,15,Fcountries, and a backlog of human
OL,16,Frights appeals against deportation,
OL,17,Fare understood to have contributed to
OL,18,Fthe increase in offenders awaiting
OL,19,Fdeportation.
